cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new model that considers relations between individual body parts, which involves learning from data, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses contrastive features, which is a technique used in multimedia retrieval, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. The paper also proposes a new method for obtaining a global feature of a person image, which involves optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Finally, the paper also discusses the effectiveness of their approach on discriminative person representations, which involves security and privacy, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible category.
